             sworn.</p>
               <p>Examined by Mr. Jackson. I am parish clerk of Mary-le-bonne, (producing the register of the marriage of the prisoner, by banns, to Catherine Hough). I witnessed it myself, I don't recollect the party; it is dated the 14th of July, 1788.</p>
               <p>MARGARET ROBSON sworn.</p>
               <p>Examined by Mr. Raine. I know the prisoner at the bar, he married my sister, I was present at the marriage, it was in the year 1788; that is the man, I attested the marriage, and my hand-writing is in the book.</p>
               <p>Q. Is your sister now living? - A. Yes, she is.</p>
               <p>The Reverend 
               <persName id="t17960406-7-person106">
                  GRIFFITH
                   GRIFFITHS
               <interp inst="t17960406-7-person106" type="surname" value="GRIFFITHS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17960406-7-person106" type="given" value="GRIFFITH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17960406-7-person106" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>Examined by Mr. Jackson. I am curate of St. Paul, Shadwell, (Produces the register of the marriage.)</p>
               <p>Q. Do you find in that register the marriage of Thomas Shuttleworth with Ann Ludgate? - A. Yes; (reads,) Thomas Shuttleworth, of this parish, a widower, to 
               <persName id="t17960406-7-person107">
                  Ann
                   Ludgate
               <interp inst="t17960406-7-person107" type="surname" value="Ludgate"></interp>
